        <div class="faq-grid">
          <article class="faq-item">
            <h3>Who is the best real estate agent in Titirangi?</h3>
            <p>The best real estate agent in Titirangi understands what makes the suburb genuinely different — the character homes, the lifestyle appeal, the specific buyer types and the complexity of pricing properties that are all highly individual. Edita Andrijasevic from Raine &amp; Horne specialises in Titirangi and surrounding West Auckland suburbs, with a 5.0 Google rating from 49 local sellers and buyers.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="faq-item">
            <h3>Why are Titirangi homes harder to price than other suburbs?</h3>
            <p>Titirangi properties are highly individual. Two houses on the same street can vary enormously in value depending on bush outlook, section gradient, access, sunlight, architectural character, renovation quality and view. Online estimates often miss these variables completely. A local appraisal from an agent who knows Titirangi specifically — and has assessed comparable properties recently — is the only reliable way to understand where your home sits in the current market.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="faq-item">
            <h3>How long does it take to sell a house in Titirangi?</h3>
            <p>Titirangi attracts a specific buyer who values lifestyle, character and community. That pool is narrower than a mainstream suburban market, which means positioning, presentation and marketing reach matter more. A well-prepared, accurately priced Titirangi home marketed to the right audience can sell within a standard 3–4 week campaign. Properties that are overpriced or poorly positioned for the right buyer type can take significantly longer.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="faq-item">
            <h3>What types of buyers look in Titirangi?</h3>
            <p>Titirangi attracts buyers who specifically want what the suburb offers: bush surroundings, character homes, a village community and a lifestyle that feels different from mainstream Auckland. Common buyer groups include families seeking space and a strong school community, city escapees wanting a lifestyle change, creatives and professionals drawn to the village character, and downsizers looking for something unique with soul rather than a standard low-maintenance unit.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="faq-item">
            <h3>What is the average house price in Titirangi?</h3>
            <p>Titirangi house prices vary widely depending on section size, bush setting, views, condition, architectural character, access and specific street location. Because no two Titirangi properties are alike, an average price figure is rarely meaningful for your individual home. For a realistic current appraisal, <a href="/free-home-appraisal-titirangi/" style="color:#9b6b00; font-weight:900; text-decoration:underline;">contact Edita for a free local assessment</a>.</p>
